\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Unit\cf0  \cf3 Generators
\f1\b0\fs28 \cf0 \
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural
\cf3 A\cf0  unit generator is an object that processes or generates sound. \cf3 There\cf0  are many\
classes of unit generators, all of which derive from the class \cf3 UGen\cf0 .  \cf3 Unit\cf0  generators in \cf3 SuperCollider\cf0  can have many inputs, but always have a single output.   \cf3 The\cf0  convention of having only a single output per unit generator allows the implementation of multiple channels by using arrays of unit generators.
\fs24 \
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 .ar
\f1\b0\fs28  (audio-rate) and 
\f0\b\fs36 .kr
\f1\b0\fs28  (control-rate)
\fs24 \
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\fs28 \cf3 A\cf0  unit generator is created by sending the \cf4 'ar'\cf0  or \cf4 'kr'\cf0  message to the unit generator\cf4 's class object. The '\cf0 ar\cf4 ' message creates a unit generator that runs at audio rate. The '\cf0 kr\cf4 ' message creates a unit generator that runs at control rate. Control rate unit generators are used for low frequency or slowly changing control signals. Control rate unit generators produce only\
a single sample per buffer and therefore use less processing power than audio rate unit generators.\
\
You can do math operations on unit generators and the result will be another unit generator. Doing math on unit generators is not doing any signal calculation itself - it is building the network of unit generators that will execute once they are played in a Synth. This is the essential thing to understand: Synthesis networks, or in other words signal flow graphs, are created by executing expressions of unit generators.\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs36 \cf4 Synth
\f1\b0\fs28  - A Synth is a collection of Ugens that run together.  The Synth plays the sound that the SynthDef has defined.\
\

\f0\b\fs36 SynthDef
\f1\b0\fs28 (synthDefName,ugenGraphFunc)\
	Defines a synthesis function that can be run by a Server.  The first argument is it'\cf0 s name, 	and the second is a \cf3 UGen\cf0  (unit-generator) function, that defines the architecture of a 	\cf3 Synth\cf0 .   \cf3 A\cf0  \cf3 SynthDef\cf0  specifies what \cf3 UGens\cf0  are used and how they are patched together.  \cf3 It\cf0  	also specifies what inputs the \cf3 Synth\cf0  will have.  \cf3 It\cf0  writes a synthDef file which the server can 	read, and a \cf3 Synth\cf0  can then be created by specifying the synthDefName. \
\

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Bus
\f1\b0\fs28 \cf0 	\cf3 A\cf0  \cf3 Bus\cf0  represents an audio or control bus on a server.  \cf3 Synths\cf0  send audio signals to each other via a single global array of \cf3 Audio\cf0  \cf3 Buses\cf0 .  \cf3 Audio\cf0  buses are indexed by integers beginning with zero. \cf3 The\cf0  lowest numbered buses get written to the audio hardware outputs.    \cf3 Bus\cf0 .index = 0 is normally the left channel, and \cf3 Bus\cf0 .index = 1 the right channel of the stereo output, and inputs work in the same way.  \cf3 The\cf0  number of input and output \cf3 Buses\cf0  are defined by you, and are the means to routing audio signals in and out of the computer.  \cf3 Control\cf0  \cf3 Buses\cf0  are a common means for \cf3 Synths\cf0  to control each other, or for \cf3 SCLang\cf0  (the user-interface language) to control \cf3 Synths\cf0  while they run.\
\

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Buffer\cf0   
\f1\b0\fs28 \cf3 Buffers\cf0  are arrays of 32 bit floating point values with a small descriptive header. \cf3 Buffers\cf0  are stored in a single global array indexed by integers beginning with zero. \cf3 Buffers\cf0  may be safely allocated, loaded and freed while synthesis is running, even while unit generators are using them. \cf3 Buffers\cf0  are used for wave tables, sample buffers, delay lines, envelopes, or for any other need which can use an array of floating point values. \cf3 Sound\cf0  files may be loaded into or written from buffers.
\f0\b\fs36 \
